items.title: <center>Consent form to take part in the study entitled “impressions of novel objects” conducted online on Prolific</center>
items.content:
Dear participant,

We are researchers from the Friedrich-Schiller-Universität Jena (Germany) and from the Université catholique de Louvain (Belgium). We are conducting a research study to examine how we form impressions of novel objects. Participation in this study will involve completing a survey. Your involvement will require about 15 minutes. You will receive £ 2.25 (~ $ US 2.80) for participating.

There are no known or anticipated risks to you for participating. Although this study will not benefit you personally, we hope that our results will add to the knowledge about psychology and evaluative learning in particular.

Please do note that some of the pictures that you will be exposed to can be of a disturbing nature (including, but not limited to: cockroaches, accidents, fire).

The researcher will not know your name, and no identifying information will be connected to your survey answers in any way. The survey is therefore anonymous.

Your responses will be numbered and stored on a password-protected computer hard drive. The information you provide will be kept until publication. A data file containing your anonymous responses (without your Prolific ID) will be stored in a secure online archive (i.e., the Open Science Framework). This data file will be available to other researchers without time limit.

Participation in this study is completely voluntary. You are free to decline to participate, to end participation at any time for any reason, or to refuse to answer any individual question without penalty or loss of compensation.

If you want a copy of the consent form, click on the "Download consent form" button below (it will open a new tab in your browser; then go back to the experiment tab):

Do you understand this consent form, agree with it, and want to participate in the study?

Investigators:

Dr. Karoline Bading, Friedrich-Schiller-Universität Jena
Friedrich Schiller University Jena, 07743 Jena, Germany
karoline.bading@uni-jena.de

Dr. Jérémy Béna, UCLouvain
jeremy.bena@uclouvain.be

Prof. Klaus Rothermund, Friedrich-Schiller-Universität Jena
klaus.rothermund@uni-jena.de

As you do not wish to participate in this study, please press the Esc key 
and return your submission on Prolific by selecting the 'Stop without completing' button.

Thank you for your comprehension.

items.title: Before you start...
items.content:
Before you start, please switch off phone/e-mail/music so you can focus on this study.

Also, make sure you are using a computer to take part in this study.

Thank you!

content.text:
The experiment consists of three parts and will take about 15 minutes.

Please read the following instructions attentively and perform all tasks 
carefully and with due focus.


Press the spacebar to continue.

Next, you will be presented with the nonword-image pairs.

Please pay close attention to each pair. 

This part of the experiment will take about 2.5 minutes.


Press the spacebar to start the task.

Whenever you classify a nonword as "old", you will be asked to perform a second task.

In this second task, you will be presented with eight images. 
Your task will be to select the image with which the nonword was previously paired with.

If you can remember the paired image, click on it and then click on the "continue" button 
at the bottom of the screen.

If you cannot remember the previously paired image, try to guess the correct one. 
Again, click on the image corresponding to your guess and then on the "continue" button
at the bottom of the screen.


Ready? Then press the spacebar to continue.

Thank you very much for your participation!

Your voluntary participation makes an important contribution to a developing
body of knowledge in psychological science.

Without volunteer participants like you, the research we are doing would not be possible 
and we want to thank you for this contribution.

Press the spacebar to continue.

items.title: If you have any comments feel free to include them below:

content.text:
In the third part of the experiment, you will again be presented with the nonwords.

This time you will be asked to express your personal evaluation of the presented nonwords.

To do so, you will be presented with an 8-point scale
ranging from very negative (left) to very positive (right).

Please click on the scale point that best represents your evaluation of a given nonword.
Then click on the "continue" button to proceed to the next nonword.


Ready? Then press the space bar to continue.

In the first part of the experiment you will be presented with nonword-image pairs.

The nonword will always be presented on the right,
and the image will always be presented on the left.

Your task is simply to pay close attention to each nonword-image pair.


Press the spacebar to continue with the instructions.

In the second part of the experiment you will be presented with individual nonwords.

Some of these nonwords were part of the previously presented pairs.

Other nonwords will be new: they were not part of the nonword-image pairs you saw in the
previous task.

For each nonword, please indicate whether it is
"old" (i.e., part of the previously presented nonword-image pairs) or
"new" (i.e., not part of the previously presented nonword-image pairs).


Press the spacebar to continue.

32.title: end_study_redirect
32.content:
The experiment is now over. Thank you very much for your participation!

In this experiment, we wanted to see whether the valence of the paired image (positive vs. negative) has an influence on your evaluation of the nonwords. In addition, we were also interested in your memory for the nonword-image pairs.

If you have any question or comment, or if you would like to receive additional information on the present study, please do not hesitate to contact the person in charge of this research at the following e-mail address: karoline.bading@uni-jena.de

Press the spacebar to be redirected to Prolific.

items.title: Vielen Dank für die Teilnahme an unserer Studie!

items.content:
Mit der Studie wollten wir untersuchen, ob Deine Einstellung zu den Gesichtern durch die Valenz der gepaarten Szenerie (positiv vs. negativ) beeinflusst wird. Außerdem wollten wir wissen, ob deine Einstellung zu den Gesichtern davon abhängt, ob Du Dich an die gepaarte Szenerie erinnern kannst.

Falls Du noch Fragen zur Studie hast, kannst Du Dich gerne an karoline.bading@uni-jena.de wenden.

Wenn Du an der FSU Jena Psychologie studierst und für die Teilnahme mit 0.5 VP-Stunden vergütet werden möchtest, kannst Du im nächsten Schritt einen Absolvierungscode für die Verbuchung im VPHS generieren. ACHTUNG: Die Absolvierungscodes werden erst nach Abschluss der Datenerhebung (Ende Februar 2023) im VPHS freigeschaltet. Eine Verbuchung Deiner 0.5 VP-Stunden wird also erst ab Anfang März 2023 möglich sein.

Hast Du noch irgendwelche Fragen oder Anmerkungen, die Du uns mitteilen möchtest? Dann trage sie gerne in das folgende Textfeld ein.

items.title: Möchtest Du einen Absolvierungscode generieren?
items.content:
Mit diesem kannst Du dann Deine Teilnahme auf dem Versuchspersonenstundenserver VPHS verbuchen.
Für die Teilnahme erhältst Du 0.5 VP-Stunden.

BEISPIEL: Für eine Person mit Geburtsort Hamburg und Handynummer 0163-78965498 lautet der Code: 181_HAM498
